peopleAlsoAsk.question: Can I use stamps that are 20 years old?
peopleAlsoAsk.snippet: You may use old stamps to mail a letter if they have not been previously used. For mailing purposes, most stamps retain their face value and do not expire. Forever stamps are worth the current rate of postage, regardless of their age.
